E5


[Verse 1]
E5
  Here I lay, still and breathless just like always. Still I want some more.
Mirrors sideways, who cares what's behind, just like always. Still your passenger.

E5
  Chrome buttons, buckles and leather surfaces. These and other lucky witnesses now, to calm me.
                          D5
This time won't you please  drive faster?


[Chorus]
E5

Let the whole world look in, who cares who sees anything?
I'm your passenger,
I'm your passenger.


[Verse 3]
E5
Drop these down, put them on me.
Nice cool seats there to cushion your knees.
Now to calm me, take me around again, don't pull over.
                          D5
This time would you please  drive faster?


[Chorus]
E5
Roll the windows down, this cool night air is curious.
Let the whole world look in, who cares who sees what tonight?
Roll these misty windows down to catch my breath, and then go and go and go.
                                  E5
Just drive me home and back again.


[Interlude]
E5


[Verse 4]
E5
  Here I lay just like always.
Go, go, go, go, go, go, go, go, go. Take me to the edge.


[Outro]
D5 F5
